  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Right now most `trie.py` files import the previous fork's implementation like this:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport ethereum.muir_glacier.trie\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd use it like this:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nreturn ethereum.muir_glacier.trie.encode_node(node, storage_root)\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nUnfortunately this has two unfortunate side effects:\r\n\r\n - Two lines change in the diff instead of one; and\r\n - `ethereum-spec-lint` can't catch incorrectly referenced forks.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThe solution to both would be to do something like:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom ethereum.muir_glacier import trie as previous_trie\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nreturn previous_trie.encode_node(node, storage_root)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat way the diff is cleaner, and the linter can detect if the previous fork import isn't actually used.",
